explanation: The code read each line with input() but did not strip newline/whitespace. If inputs include trailing spaces or other invisible characters, comparisons (including reversed strings) can fail. I fixed the single incorrect line by stripping whitespace from the input: S = input().strip().
fixed_code:
N = int(input())

Z = set()

count = 0
for i in range(N):
    S = input().strip()
    if S in Z:
        count += 1
    Z.add(S)
    Z.add(S[::-1])

print(count)
